# Supply Chain Management System - Cursor Rules

## Project Structure

### Backend (Django)
- @backend/supply_chain/settings.py - Main Django settings
- @backend/supply_chain/urls.py - Main URL routing
- @backend/apps/*/models.py - Django models for each app
- @backend/apps/*/views.py - API views for each app
- @backend/apps/*/serializers.py - Data serialization
- @backend/apps/*/urls.py - App-specific URL routing
- @backend/ml/*.py - Machine learning modules

### Frontend (Next.js)
- @frontend/app/*.tsx - Next.js pages and layouts
- @frontend/components/*.tsx - Reusable React components
- @frontend/hooks/*.ts - Custom React hooks
- @frontend/utils/*.ts - Utility functions
- @frontend/styles/*.css - Global styles and Tailwind

### Documentation
- @.cursor/rules/*.md - Project rules and guidelines
- @docs/architecture.md - System architecture
- @docs/api/*.md - API documentation

## Naming Conventions

### Backend
- Use snake_case for Python files and functions
- Use PascalCase for Django models and classes
- Use kebab-case for URL patterns
- Use UPPERCASE for environment variables

### Frontend
- Use PascalCase for React components and TypeScript types
- Use camelCase for JavaScript/TypeScript variables and functions
- Use kebab-case for CSS classes and Tailwind utilities
- Use snake_case for file names

